      <div class="q-card" id="card-o1">
        <div class="q-num">Question 1</div>
        <div class="q-text">What happens to RBCs in a <span class="key">hypertonic</span> solution?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o1',false)">They swell and burst</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o1',true)">They shrink (crenate)</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o1',false)">They stay the same</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o1',false)">They divide</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="o1-fb">They crenate — hypertonic = more solutes outside, so water exits the cell by osmosis causing it to shrivel.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-o2">
        <div class="q-num">Question 2</div>
        <div class="q-text">What happens to RBCs in a <span class="key">hypotonic</span> solution?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o2',false)">They crenate</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o2',false)">They stay normal</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o2',true)">They lyse (burst)</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o2',false)">They release starch</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="o2-fb">They lyse — hypotonic = fewer solutes outside, so water rushes INTO the cell, the membrane ruptures and releases hemoglobin.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-o3">
        <div class="q-num">Question 3</div>
        <div class="q-text">Why don't we give dehydrated patients <span class="key">distilled water</span>?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o3',false)">It's too expensive</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o3',false)">It would cause cells to crenate</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o3',true)">It's hypotonic — cells would absorb water and burst</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o3',false)">It has no oxygen</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="o3-fb">DI water is hypotonic (no solutes). Cells would take in water rapidly and lyse. Normal saline (0.9% NaCl) is used because it's isotonic to blood.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-o4">
        <div class="q-num">Question 4</div>
        <div class="q-text">In an <span class="key">isotonic</span> solution, what happens to RBCs?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o4',false)">They shrink</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o4',false)">They burst</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o4',true)">They maintain normal shape and size</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o4',false)">They release hemoglobin</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="o4-fb">Normal shape and size — isotonic = equal solute concentration inside and outside, so no net water movement occurs.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-o5">
        <div class="q-num">Question 5</div>
        <div class="q-text">Which ion contributes approximately <span class="key">50%</span> of total osmolarity of human body fluids?</div>
