          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o5',false)">Chloride (Cl-)</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'o5',false)">Bicarbonate (HCO3-)</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="o5-fb">Sodium — contributes ~50% of total osmolarity on its own. Na+, Cl-, and HCO3- together account for about 90%.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- REFLEXES -->
    <div class="sub-panel2" id="sub2-reflex">
      <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:0">Neuromuscular Reflexes — Multiple Choice</div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-r1">
        <div class="q-num">Question 1</div>
        <div class="q-text">Which is <span class="key">NOT</span> a component of a reflex arc?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r1',false)">Receptor</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r1',false)">Sensory (afferent) neuron</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r1',true)">Brain</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r1',false)">Effector</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="r1-fb">The brain — simple reflexes bypass the brain entirely. The arc goes: receptor → sensory neuron → interneuron (spinal cord) → motor neuron → effector. Brain is informed after the fact.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-r2">
        <div class="q-num">Question 2</div>
        <div class="q-text">Complete the reflex arc order:<br><span class="key">Receptor → ? → Interneuron → ? → Effector</span></div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r2',false)">Motor neuron → Sensory neuron</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r2',true)">Sensory neuron → Motor neuron</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r2',false)">Brain → Spinal cord</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r2',false)">Interneuron → Sensory neuron</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="r2-fb">Sensory (afferent) carries signal IN to the spinal cord. Motor (efferent) carries signal OUT to the muscle/effector.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-r3">
        <div class="q-num">Question 3</div>
        <div class="q-text">A reflex grade of <span class="key">4+</span> indicates what?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r3',false)">Normal brisk response</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r3',false)">Slight but present — may be normal</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r3',false)">No response — always abnormal</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r3',true)">Repeating reflex (clonus) — always abnormal</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="r3-fb">4+ = clonus — always abnormal. Grade 0 is also always abnormal. Grade 2+ is normal. 1+ and 3+ may or may not be normal.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-r4">
        <div class="q-num">Question 4</div>
        <div class="q-text">In normal <span class="key">adults</span>, what is the expected Babinski response?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r4',false)">Big toe dorsiflexes and toes fan out</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r4',true)">Toes flex downward</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r4',false)">No response at all</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r4',false)">Leg kicks forward</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="r4-fb">Toes flex downward — normal in adults. Fanning/dorsiflexion (Babinski's sign) is normal in infants (unmyelinated nerves) but abnormal in adults.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-r5">
        <div class="q-num">Question 5</div>
        <div class="q-text">Which reflex grade is considered <span class="key">normal</span>?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r5',false)">0</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r5',false)">1+</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r5',true)">2+</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r5',false)">4+</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="r5-fb">2+ is the normal brisk response. 0 is always abnormal. 4+ is always abnormal. 1+ and 3+ depend on patient history.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-label">Identify the Reflex</div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-r6">
        <div class="q-num">Question 6</div>
        <div class="q-text">Tapping just below the kneecap causes the leg to kick forward. What reflex is this?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r6',false)">Achilles reflex</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r6',true)">Patellar reflex</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r6',false)">Bicep reflex</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r6',false)">Plantar reflex</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="r6-fb">Patellar reflex — tapping the patellar tendon stretches the quadriceps, triggering a contraction and leg extension. Tests spinal cord levels L3–L4.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-r7">
        <div class="q-num">Question 7</div>
        <div class="q-text">Tapping the Achilles tendon causes the foot to plantarflex. What reflex is this and what spinal levels does it test?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r7',false)">Patellar reflex — L3-L4</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r7',false)">Tricep reflex — C6-C7</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r7',true)">Achilles reflex — S1-S2</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r7',false)">Plantar reflex — L4-L5</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="r7-fb">Achilles reflex — tapping the Achilles tendon triggers the gastrocnemius (calf) to contract, causing plantarflexion (foot points down). Tests S1–S2 of the sacral spinal cord.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-r8">
        <div class="q-num">Question 8</div>
        <div class="q-text">Tapping the bicep tendon at the elbow causes the forearm to flex. What spinal levels does this test?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r8',false)">L3-L4</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r8',false)">S1-S2</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r8',true)">C5-C6</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r8',false)">C8-T1</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="r8-fb">Bicep reflex tests C5–C6. The bicep contracts and the forearm flexes. Loss of this reflex can indicate damage to the cervical spinal cord at that level.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-r9">
        <div class="q-num">Question 9</div>
        <div class="q-text">Tapping the tricep tendon above the elbow causes forearm extension. What spinal levels does the tricep reflex test?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r9',false)">C4-C5</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r9',true)">C6-C7</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r9',false)">T1-T2</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r9',false)">L1-L2</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="r9-fb">Tricep reflex tests C6–C7. The tricep contracts and the forearm extends. This is the opposite movement from the bicep reflex.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-r10">
        <div class="q-num">Question 10</div>
        <div class="q-text">The <span class="key">brachioradialis reflex</span> is triggered by tapping where?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r10',false)">The back of the upper arm</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r10',false)">The inside of the elbow</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r10',true)">The forearm / wrist area near the radius</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'r10',false)">The palm of the hand</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="r10-fb">Brachioradialis reflex — tapping the brachioradialis tendon near the wrist/lower forearm causes forearm flexion. Tests C5–C6, similar to the bicep reflex.</div>
      </div>

