    <!-- URINALYSIS -->
    <div class="sub-panel2" id="sub2-urine">
      <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:0">Urinalysis — Multiple Choice</div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-u1">
        <div class="q-num">Question 1</div>
        <div class="q-text">What might <span class="key">glucose</span> in urine indicate?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u1',false)">Liver disease</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u1',true)">Diabetes</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u1',false)">Kidney infection</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u1',false)">Dehydration</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="u1-fb">Diabetes — blood glucose exceeds the kidney's reabsorption threshold so it spills into urine. Normally zero glucose should appear in urine.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-u2">
        <div class="q-num">Question 2</div>
        <div class="q-text">Why is <span class="key">first morning urine</span> ideal for urinalysis?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u2',false)">Easier to collect</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u2',true)">Most concentrated</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u2',false)">Fewer bacteria</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u2',false)">More acidic</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="u2-fb">Most concentrated — no fluid intake overnight means higher ADH, more water reabsorption, and more concentrated urine. Easier to detect abnormal substances.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-u3">
        <div class="q-num">Question 3</div>
        <div class="q-text"><span class="key">High specific gravity</span> in urine most likely indicates:</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u3',false)">Kidney infection</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u3',false)">Overhydration</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u3',true)">Dehydration / concentrated urine</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u3',false)">Normal hydration</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="u3-fb">Dehydration — high SG means many solutes per volume of water = concentrated urine = dehydrated patient. Low SG = dilute urine = overhydrated.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-u4">
        <div class="q-num">Question 4</div>
        <div class="q-text">Is it normal to find <span class="key">epithelial cells</span> in urine?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u4',false)">No — always abnormal</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u4',true)">Yes — small numbers are normal</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u4',false)">Only in women</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u4',false)">Only if infected</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="u4-fb">Small numbers are normal — epithelial cells naturally shed from the urinary tract lining. Only large amounts or abnormal types are clinically significant.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-u5">
        <div class="q-num">Question 5</div>
        <div class="q-text">Urine positive for <span class="key">albumin (protein)</span> might indicate:</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u5',false)">Diabetes</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u5',false)">Dehydration</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u5',true)">Kidney damage or disease</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u5',false)">Normal — protein is always present</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="u5-fb">Kidney damage — healthy kidneys retain protein in the blood. Protein leaking into urine suggests the glomerular filtration barrier is damaged.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-card" id="card-u6">
        <div class="q-num">Question 6</div>
        <div class="q-text">Distilled water has a SG of 1.000. What does a reading of <span class="key">1.030</span> suggest compared to 1.005?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u6',true)">1.030 = more concentrated / more dehydrated</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u6',false)">1.005 = more concentrated / more dehydrated</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u6',false)">They mean the same thing</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'u6',false)">1.030 = overhydrated</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="u6-fb">1.030 = more concentrated — higher SG means more solutes per volume of water. Further above 1.000 = more concentrated = more dehydrated.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- EMG -->
    <div class="sub-panel2" id="sub2-emg">
      <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:0">EMG — Questions</div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-e1">
        <div class="q-num">Question 1</div>
        <div class="q-text">What does <span class="key">EMG</span> measure?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e1',false)">Force produced by a muscle</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e1',true)">Electrical activity of muscle contractions</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e1',false)">Oxygen consumption in muscle</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e1',false)">Speed of nerve conduction</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="e1-fb">Electrical activity — EMG (electromyography) records the electrical signals produced when muscle fibers contract. Measured in millivolts (mV).</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-e2">
        <div class="q-num">Question 2</div>
        <div class="q-text">What is a <span class="key">motor unit</span>?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e2',false)">A group of muscles working together</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e2',true)">One motor neuron + all the muscle fibers it controls</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e2',false)">The minimum force needed to contract a muscle</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e2',false)">A single muscle fiber</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="e2-fb">One motor neuron + all the muscle fibers it innervates. When the neuron fires, ALL fibers in that unit contract together (all-or-none principle).</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-e3">
        <div class="q-num">Question 3</div>
        <div class="q-text">Which motor units are recruited <span class="key">first</span> and why?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e3',false)">Largest — they produce the most force</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e3',true)">Smallest — they have the lowest activation threshold</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e3',false)">Random — there is no order</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e3',false)">Largest — they fatigue slowest</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="e3-fb">Smallest first — they have the lowest activation threshold so they fire with minimal stimulus. Larger units are added as more force is needed (size principle).</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-e4">
        <div class="q-num">True or False</div>
        <div class="q-text">Surface electrodes can isolate a <span class="key">single motor unit</span>.</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e4',false)">True</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e4',true)">False</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="e4-fb">False — surface electrodes pick up multiple motor units at once. Needle electrodes are needed to isolate individual motor units with precision.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-e5">
        <div class="q-num">True or False</div>
        <div class="q-text">As grip force increases, EMG signal <span class="key">increases</span>.</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e5',true)">True</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e5',false)">False</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="e5-fb">True — positive linear relationship. More force requires more motor unit recruitment, which produces more electrical activity = higher EMG signal.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-e6">
        <div class="q-num">Fill in the blank</div>
        <div class="q-text">The process of activating more motor units as force demand increases is called ________.</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e6',false)">Depolarization</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e6',true)">Motor unit recruitment</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e6',false)">Muscle fatigue</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'e6',false)">Interference pattern</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="e6-fb">Motor unit recruitment — the nervous system progressively activates more and larger motor units to generate increasing levels of force.</div>
      </div>

