      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:8px;margin-bottom:8px;">
        <div class="match-col-lbl">Term</div><div class="match-col-lbl">Definition</div>
      </div>
      <div class="match-cols" id="mmemg-left-wrap" style="display:contents;"></div>
      <div class="match-complete" id="mmemg-complete">All matched!</div>

      <div class="section-label">Muscle Fatigue — Questions</div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-mf1">
        <div class="q-num">Question 1</div>
        <div class="q-text">Define <span class="key">muscle fatigue</span>.</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf1',false)">The complete inability of a muscle to contract</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf1',true)">A decline in force output during sustained or repeated contraction</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf1',false)">Muscle damage caused by overuse</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf1',false)">The resting state of a muscle between contractions</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="mf1-fb">Muscle fatigue is the progressive decline in a muscle's ability to generate force during sustained or repeated contractions — even though stimulation continues.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-mf2">
        <div class="q-num">Question 2</div>
        <div class="q-text">Which of the following is <span class="key">NOT</span> a cause of muscle fatigue?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf2',false)">ATP and glycogen depletion</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf2',false)">Lactic acid and H+ ion buildup</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf2',false)">Impaired calcium release from the sarcoplasmic reticulum</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf2',true)">Increased motor unit recruitment</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="mf2-fb">Increased motor unit recruitment actually helps fight fatigue — it's a compensation strategy. The three main causes are ATP/glycogen depletion, metabolic byproduct buildup (lactic acid, H+), and impaired calcium release.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-mf3">
        <div class="q-num">Question 3</div>
        <div class="q-text">Why does <span class="key">force decrease</span> as a muscle fatigues?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf3',false)">The motor neuron stops sending signals</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf3',true)">ATP runs low, metabolic byproducts accumulate, and calcium release is impaired — all reducing the muscle's ability to contract</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf3',false)">The muscle fibers physically tear during contraction</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf3',false)">Threshold stimulus increases permanently</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="mf3-fb">Without enough ATP, cross-bridges can't cycle. H+ ions from lactic acid interfere with myosin-actin binding. Impaired Ca2+ release means fewer fibers activate. All three together reduce force output progressively.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-mf4">
        <div class="q-num">Question 4</div>
        <div class="q-text">How would a <span class="key">bodybuilder's</span> time to fatigue compare to an average person's?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf4',false)">Shorter — more muscle mass means more ATP demand</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf4',true)">Longer — more muscle fibers, greater glycogen stores, and more efficient energy systems</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf4',false)">The same — muscle fatigue is determined by the nervous system only</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf4',false)">Shorter — larger muscles produce more lactic acid faster</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="mf4-fb">A bodybuilder would fatigue much later. Greater muscle mass = more motor units available to rotate in. More glycogen stored = more ATP available. Trained muscles also manage metabolic byproducts more efficiently.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-mf5">
        <div class="q-num">True or False</div>
        <div class="q-text">Lactic acid and H+ ion buildup is one cause of <span class="key">muscle fatigue</span>.</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf5',true)">True</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'mf5',false)">False</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="mf5-fb">True — H+ ions lower the pH inside the muscle cell, which interferes with enzyme activity and myosin-actin cross-bridge cycling, reducing force output.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

