      <div class="q-card" id="card-th1">
        <div class="q-num">Question 1</div>
        <div class="q-text">Based on Barbara's symptoms and labs, is she suffering from <span class="key">hypothyroidism or hyperthyroidism</span>?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th1',true)">Hypothyroidism</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th1',false)">Hyperthyroidism</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="th1-fb">Hypothyroidism — her T3 and T4 are both below normal range. Her thyroid is not producing enough hormone, causing every system to slow down (cold, fatigue, weight gain).</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-th2">
        <div class="q-num">Question 2</div>
        <div class="q-text">Why does Barbara feel <span class="key">cold</span>?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th2',false)">Her blood pressure is too low</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th2',true)">Low T3/T4 drops metabolic rate → less energy burned → less heat generated</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th2',false)">She has anemia</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th2',false)">Her sodium levels are too low</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="th2-fb">T3/T4 regulate metabolism. When they're low, the body's metabolic rate drops, less energy is burned, and less heat is produced as a byproduct — so the patient feels cold.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-th3">
        <div class="q-num">Question 3</div>
        <div class="q-text">Why has Barbara <span class="key">gained weight</span> without changing her diet?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th3',false)">Her glucose is elevated causing fat storage</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th3',false)">She has excess cortisol</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th3',true)">Low T3/T4 causes metabolic slowdown — fewer calories burned, more stored as fat</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th3',false)">High TSH directly causes fat storage</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="th3-fb">Low T3/T4 = metabolic slowdown. The body burns fewer calories at rest and stores the excess as fat — even with no diet change.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-th4">
        <div class="q-num">Question 4</div>
        <div class="q-text">Where is <span class="key">TSH</span> released from, and what does it stand for?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th4',false)">Thyroid — Thyroid Stimulating Hormone</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th4',false)">Hypothalamus — Thyroid Stimulating Hormone</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th4',true)">Pituitary — Thyroid Stimulating Hormone</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th4',false)">Adrenal gland — Thyroid Stimulating Hormone</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="th4-fb">Pituitary gland — TSH (Thyroid Stimulating Hormone) is released by the anterior pituitary in response to TRH from the hypothalamus. It tells the thyroid to produce T3 and T4.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-th5">
        <div class="q-num">Question 5</div>
        <div class="q-text">If untreated, will Barbara develop a <span class="key">goiter</span>?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th5',false)">No — goiters only form with hyperthyroidism</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th5',true)">Yes — rising TSH chronically stimulates the thyroid, causing it to enlarge</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th5',false)">No — her TSH is too low to cause a goiter</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th5',false)">Only if her T4 drops below 1.0</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="th5-fb">Yes — because T3/T4 are low, the pituitary keeps pumping out more and more TSH trying to compensate. Chronic TSH stimulation causes the thyroid gland to physically enlarge = goiter.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-th6">
        <div class="q-num">True or False</div>
        <div class="q-text">High TSH always means the patient has <span class="key">hyperthyroidism</span>.</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th6',false)">True</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th6',true)">False</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="th6-fb">False — high TSH means the pituitary is working overtime trying to stimulate a sluggish thyroid. High TSH = hypothyroidism. Low TSH = hyperthyroidism (pituitary backing off because T3/T4 are already too high).</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-th7">
        <div class="q-num">True or False</div>
        <div class="q-text">The <span class="key">hypothalamus</span> releases TRH.</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th7',true)">True</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th7',false)">False</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="th7-fb">True — TRH (Thyrotropin-Releasing Hormone) comes from the hypothalamus → tells pituitary to release TSH → TSH tells thyroid to produce T3/T4.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-th8">
        <div class="q-num">Fill in the blank</div>
        <div class="q-text">Complete the hypothalamic-pituitary-thyroid axis:<br>Hypothalamus → <span class="key">________</span> → Pituitary → <span class="key">________</span> → Thyroid → T3/T4</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th8',false)">TSH → TRH</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th8',true)">TRH → TSH</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th8',false)">T3 → T4</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'th8',false)">TSH → T3</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="th8-fb">TRH → TSH. Hypothalamus releases TRH (Thyrotropin-Releasing Hormone) → Pituitary releases TSH (Thyroid Stimulating Hormone) → Thyroid produces T3 and T4.</div>
      </div>

