    <!-- WBC LAB -->
    <div class="sub-panel2" id="sub2-wbclab">
      <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:0">WBC Lab — Questions</div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-w1">
        <div class="q-num">Question 1</div>
        <div class="q-text">What is the medical term for a <span class="key">low</span> WBC count?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w1',false)">Leukocytosis</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w1',true)">Leukopenia</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w1',false)">Anemia</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w1',false)">Thrombocytopenia</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="w1-fb">Leukopenia — "leuko" = white, "penia" = deficiency. A low WBC count means the immune system is compromised and less able to fight infection.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-w2">
        <div class="q-num">Question 2</div>
        <div class="q-text">What is the medical term for a <span class="key">high</span> WBC count?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w2',true)">Leukocytosis</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w2',false)">Leukopenia</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w2',false)">Polycythemia</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w2',false)">Leukemia only</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="w2-fb">Leukocytosis — "leuko" = white, "cytosis" = increase in cells. Usually a sign the body is fighting an infection or inflammation, but can also indicate leukemia.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-w3">
        <div class="q-num">Question 3</div>
        <div class="q-text">What is the <span class="key">normal total WBC count</span> range?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w3',false)">500–1,000 cells/μL</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w3',false)">1,000–3,000 cells/μL</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w3',true)">4,500–11,000 cells/μL</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w3',false)">15,000–20,000 cells/μL</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="w3-fb">4,500–11,000 cells/μL (or 4.5–11 × 10³/μL) — this is the normal range for a total WBC count. Don't forget the units on the exam!</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-w4">
        <div class="q-num">Question 4</div>
        <div class="q-text">Why must blood type be determined <span class="key">before surgery</span>?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w4',false)">To check if the patient is dehydrated</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w4',true)">To prevent agglutination — incompatible blood transfused during surgery can clump and block vessels</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w4',false)">To determine anesthesia dose</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w4',false)">Blood type doesn't matter during surgery</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="w4-fb">If incompatible blood is transfused, the patient's immune system attacks the donor RBCs — causing agglutination (clumping). This can block blood vessels and be life-threatening.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-w5">
        <div class="q-num">Question 5</div>
        <div class="q-text">What is <span class="key">agglutination</span>?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w5',false)">The process of making new red blood cells</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w5',false)">A type of mutation in WBCs</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w5',true)">Clumping of RBCs when incompatible blood types are mixed</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w5',false)">The breakdown of hemoglobin</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="w5-fb">Agglutination = clumping. When incompatible blood is mixed, antibodies in the recipient's blood bind to antigens on the donor's RBCs, causing them to clump together.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-w6">
        <div class="q-num">True or False</div>
        <div class="q-text">Leukopenia means a <span class="key">high</span> WBC count.</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w6',false)">True</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w6',true)">False</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="w6-fb">False — leukopenia means LOW white blood cells. "Penia" always means deficiency or decrease. Leukocytosis = high WBC count.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-w7">
        <div class="q-num">Question 7</div>
        <div class="q-text">Which of the following would most likely cause <span class="key">leukopenia</span>?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w7',false)">Bacterial infection</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w7',false)">Leukemia</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w7',true)">Chemotherapy or bone marrow disorder</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w7',false)">Allergic reaction</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="w7-fb">Chemotherapy kills rapidly dividing cells — including bone marrow stem cells that produce WBCs. Other causes include bone marrow disorders, autoimmune diseases, and some viral infections (like HIV).</div>
      </div>

      <div class="q-card" id="card-w8">
        <div class="q-num">Question 8</div>
        <div class="q-text">Which of the following would most likely cause <span class="key">leukocytosis</span>?</div>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w8',false)">Chemotherapy</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w8',false)">Bone marrow failure</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w8',true)">Bacterial infection or leukemia</button>
          <button class="opt-btn" onclick="choose(this,'w8',false)">Severe dehydration</button>
        </div>
        <div class="feedback" id="w8-fb">Bacterial infection triggers the immune system to rapidly produce more WBCs to fight the invader. Leukemia causes uncontrolled WBC production. Inflammation and stress can also cause leukocytosis.</div>
      </div>

